---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/CTASection.astro';

const title = 'Projects | Owen Air Technical Services';
const description =
  'Project-style examples of practical technical work across networking, websites, venue systems, van power planning and technical rescue on the Isle of Man.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="projects-heading">
    <div class="container flow">
      <p class="pill">Projects</p>
      <h1 class="section-title" id="projects-heading">The kind of work I take on</h1>
      <p class="section-lead">
        These are representative examples, not client testimonials. They show how I typically approach
        real-world technical problems across networking, audio, websites, power and inherited systems.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container grid grid-2">
      <article class="card flow">
        <h2>Venue Wi-Fi and secure networks</h2>
        <h3>The problem</h3>
        <p>
          A hospitality venue needs guest Wi-Fi for customers, staff Wi-Fi for internal use, and a secure
          network for card machines and POS devices.
        </p>
        <h3>What I check</h3>
        <p>
          Internet path, gateway, AP placement, VLANs, DHCP/DNS, switch ports, firewall rules, bandwidth,
          guest isolation, and payment device separation.
        </p>
        <h3>What I change or recommend</h3>
        <p>
          Separate guest, staff and secure device networks. Rate-limit guest traffic, isolate public users,
          keep payment devices away from customer traffic, and document the setup for easier support.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card flow">
        <h2>Fast Astro and Cloudflare website</h2>
        <h3>The problem</h3>
        <p>
          A local business needs a website that looks credible, loads quickly and makes it easy for people to
          make contact.
        </p>
        <h3>What I check</h3>
        <p>
          Site structure, copy clarity, service pages, contact form flow, mobile layout, SEO metadata,
          performance, deployment setup and security headers.
        </p>
        <h3>What I change or recommend</h3>
        <p>
          Build a fast Astro site on Cloudflare with clear CTAs, local SEO basics, practical contact handling,
          and straightforward future maintenance.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card flow">
        <h2>Venue audio system improvement</h2>
        <h3>The problem</h3>
        <p>
          A system is loud in some areas, weak in others, unclear when busy, and difficult to understand
          because of old equipment and poor documentation.
        </p>
        <h3>What I check</h3>
        <p>
          Speaker placement, room layout, amp and DSP routing, gain structure, crossover points, limiter
          settings, cabling, coverage zones and DJ booth monitoring.
        </p>
        <h3>What I change or recommend</h3>
        <p>
          Map the current system, identify the biggest weak points, tidy routing, set sensible DSP starting
          points, add fills where needed and plan upgrades in stages.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card flow">
        <h2>Van power planning</h2>
        <h3>The problem</h3>
        <p>
          A campervan has a basic leisure battery and solar setup, but the owner wants lithium batteries,
          bigger inverter capacity and better monitoring.
        </p>
        <h3>What I check</h3>
        <p>
          Battery type, solar controller, alternator charging, inverter sizing, cable and fuse sizing, loads,
          charging sources, monitoring and practical safety layout.
        </p>
        <h3>What I change or recommend</h3>
        <p>
          Create a phased Victron-style plan for lithium, DC-DC charging, solar integration, monitoring and
          appropriate protection, in the right order.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card flow project-wide">
        <h2>Technical rescue for inherited systems</h2>
        <h3>The problem</h3>
        <p>
          Multiple people have changed a setup over time, nobody has current notes, and faults could be
          cabling, networking, configuration, hardware, software or power.
        </p>
        <h3>What I check</h3>
        <p>
          Physical connections, device list, network routes, account access, logs, power, recent changes and
          failure patterns.
        </p>
        <h3>What I change or recommend</h3>
        <p>
          Trace and document the setup, stabilise the system, identify likely root causes, and provide a
          practical list of what to fix now versus what can be staged later.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    title="Need help with something similar?"
    text="Describe your setup and what keeps going wrong. I can usually work out what is actually happening and suggest the most sensible next step."
    primary={{ href: '/contact', label: 'Tell me what you need' }}
    secondary={{ href: '/services', label: 'View services' }}
  />
</Layout>

<style>
  h1,
  h2,
  h3 {
    margin: 0;
  }

  h3 {
    font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .project-wide {
    grid-column: span 2;
  }

  @media (max-width: 46rem) {
    .project-wide {
      grid-column: span 1;
    }
  }
</style>
